notes:
## Playstyle

- We want to play safe and farm Cash. Play behind your Tank and with your Supports, look to Dynamite above and slightly behind the enemy Tank and try your best to shoot enemies for damage and eliminations.
- Keep your Coach Gun handy to peel for yourself if the enemy has anyone getting close to you, such a Genji. Make sure to avoid having your Coach Gun deflected or denied by similar abilities.

---

## Powers:

-  [Incendiary Blast](item_2660993e-698c-4ea0-9a65-6b1fd02f38df) is the safest option to recommend. It allows you to peel for yourself if anyone gets close while making it very risky for enemies to try and jump on you, since this helps you kill them much easily. If an enemy gets close to you while you have your Dynamite, be sure to Dynamite them first and then Coach Gun, as the additional 75 damage will burst them.
-  [Early Detonation](item_9e8a8aad-96a1-4068-994c-be0d3750469b) can be an alternative option where you don't face any immediate threats on the enemy team, but be careful because you're more susceptible to being pushed.
 - This can also be a good option vs. Kiriko. It will reduce your Dynamite cooldown to 9 seconds, while Kiriko's Suzu cooldown is 14 seconds. So you can spam Dynamites while she can't keep up cleansing them.

---

## Items:

-  [Compensator](item_2a354f80-610c-4661-9bdd-8960ae1a60b0) since our build isn't online and Ashe is a hitscan hero, shooting our gun is our best way to contribute to the fight.
-  [Power Playbook](item_6d8803cf-baa7-46ee-af91-51e7f2301418) is still useful since Dynamite can have such an impact with it being AOE.
-  [Armored Vest](item_358361e2-59be-4c81-b221-8a87f37809e6) is another safe recommendation. It's important to avoid silly deaths that will result in making less income. Play it safe and smart so you can be consistent.

## Playstyle:

- You can focus a bit more on using your Dynamite for your damage now. Still make sure to shoot enemies for extra contribution to keep farming Cash.

---

## Items:

-  [Stacked Sticks](item_2ad5dace-ac3c-43fe-b20b-3add489a7207) increases how big the Dynamite explosion is, making the AOE bigger and hitting more enemies.
-  [Armored Vest](item_358361e2-59be-4c81-b221-8a87f37809e6) can help make sure we stay alive.

---

## Optional Items:

-  [Silver Lighter](item_858f4336-77ae-4a2d-b26d-cce6e939c54e) If you have a lot of extra Cash, getting Silver Lighter now is still great. Even though we don't have  [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) yet, regular B.O.B is still so strong and impactful. 
- Keep your extra Weapon Power/Ability Items from the first round if you don't have enough for Silver Lighter.

## Playstyle

- Now we're much more focused on our Dynamite. On the start of the round, don't just follow your tank, try to take an angle to get a bigger and better Dynamite on the enemy. Then run away, you can choose to go back to your team if the enemy team has anything that might try to push you (Genji, Reaper, Kiriko with [Fleet Foot](item_1d58371c-71a9-44c2-8d5a-0663467599e9)), otherwise you can look for a different angle or re-use your angle when your Dynamite is back off cooldown.
- You can still shoot your Weapon at enemies if you have the luxury, but be careful. The priority is landing your Dynamites now because you can get  [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) so quickly and help you capture first points.

---

## Power

-  [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) allows our build to come online now. We want to throw him onto the point, ideally where he has some cover or is alongside your Tank, so that the enemies can't focus him without being punished. 
- Bob will last much longer too, so don't worry about him not doing much damage, because he'll help capture/contest the objective.

---

## Item

-  [Silver Lighter](item_858f4336-77ae-4a2d-b26d-cce6e939c54e) will help our Dynamite farm even much Ultimate Charge to get  [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) online quicker.
-  [Nano Cola](item_79b22609-8046-4a8a-a5a2-bb49cd7e11c6) is extra AP for more damage from our Dynamite.

---

## Optional Item

-  [Multi-Tool](item_5ba8d94e-f2f3-44b7-8773-025fc6ed7c56) is an acceptable alternative if unable to afford [Nano Cola](item_79b22609-8046-4a8a-a5a2-bb49cd7e11c6).
- Leftover Cash should be spent on [Power Playbook](item_6d8803cf-baa7-46ee-af91-51e7f2301418), [Charged Plating](item_b8ca58e7-6ae2-40ee-8618-fe2f32315295), or [Armored Vest](item_358361e2-59be-4c81-b221-8a87f37809e6).

--

## Additional Notice

With [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) halving our Ultimate Charge required,  [Furnace Fuel](item_aac67acc-e7d0-4465-b3d3-1276a6de0f86) loses a ton of value, since 3% Ultimate Charge means even less since we've just halved the ult cost we need already.

## Playstyle

We continue with our playstyle from the last round:
- focusing on landing big dynamites, taking angles to help us do this and then playing safe until we have dynamite available again
- using coach gun to ward off flankers
- If there are no enemy threats to worry about, you can apply burn using Coach Gun first and then Dynamite to maximise our 20% increased damage from [Infrared Lenses](item_f19df350-745e-4e97-a495-8036b0be1262). 
 - This can leave you more vulnerable to being pushed, so I only recommend it when your next Dynamite will give you Ult.

---

## Items

-  [Infrared Lenses](item_f19df350-745e-4e97-a495-8036b0be1262) Increases our damage when using either of our abilities. We sell [Nano Cola](item_79b22609-8046-4a8a-a5a2-bb49cd7e11c6) to help us afford this.
-  [Custom Stock](item_17d633af-8bcc-4893-b865-be0a7bc66fe2) is a great item to use our leftover Cash.

---

## Optional Items

-  [Catalytic Crystal](item_3e3f4f77-cdf8-4dda-a5b0-2fb9390aefc4) can replace  [Infrared Lenses](item_f19df350-745e-4e97-a495-8036b0be1262), but I believe Infrared Lenses is better because the increased damage to burning targets will grant you more Ultimate Charge anyway.
- If you have 6,000 Cash remaining, then keep [Nano Cola](item_79b22609-8046-4a8a-a5a2-bb49cd7e11c6) instead of getting [Custom Stock](item_17d633af-8bcc-4893-b865-be0a7bc66fe2).
-  [Multi-Tool](item_5ba8d94e-f2f3-44b7-8773-025fc6ed7c56) is an alternative option to  [Custom Stock](item_17d633af-8bcc-4893-b865-be0a7bc66fe2) - but I think the 5% Weapon Power  5% Cooldown Reduction as that doesn't even reduce the Dynamite cooldown by 1 second. The increased Weapon Power will work well with [Infrared Lenses](item_f19df350-745e-4e97-a495-8036b0be1262) too.
- Extra remaining Cash should be spend on  [Power Playbook](item_6d8803cf-baa7-46ee-af91-51e7f2301418) and  [Charged Plating](item_b8ca58e7-6ae2-40ee-8618-fe2f32315295).

## Power

- [Double Barrelled](item_962b847f-140d-41a4-9bac-ddcdb088951e) allows us to make better use of [Incendiary Blast](item_2660993e-698c-4ea0-9a65-6b1fd02f38df).
 - We can use our extra Coach Gun to either apply an initial burn for our Dynamite explosion to do 20% increased damage with [Infrared Lenses](item_f19df350-745e-4e97-a495-8036b0be1262), or use it to follow up on a Dynamite to do the additional 75 damage instantly.
- We can choose to greedily use both Coach Guns for a burst combo, but remember that this leaves us vulnerable as Coach Gun is an important defensive tool.

---

## Items

- [Catalytic Crystal](item_3e3f4f77-cdf8-4dda-a5b0-2fb9390aefc4) can give us an extra 20% Ultimate Charge and combined with our other items, we should now be able to get  [B.O.B Jr.](item_a0599423-2cd6-4779-81c1-fb933fbad07d) online with as little as 2 uses of Dynamite.
- Extra Cash should be spent on  [Power Playbook](item_6d8803cf-baa7-46ee-af91-51e7f2301418), [Charged Plating](item_b8ca58e7-6ae2-40ee-8618-fe2f32315295), [Custom Stock](item_17d633af-8bcc-4893-b865-be0a7bc66fe2) or  [Nano Cola](item_79b22609-8046-4a8a-a5a2-bb49cd7e11c6).

## Items

- [Liquid Nitrogen](item_a8d99526-05a3-4405-babb-b025479b1b98) makes your burns apply a 20% slow and yes, they're slowed for entire burn and the 2 seconds after the burn ends! It's so incredibly annoying!

---

## Optional Items

- [Cybervenom](item_210a8582-91ec-4cf3-968a-a443f3a0c505) is another great option because enemies will have the heal reduction for your entire burn too. But ideally, you should have a teammate who applies this instead, especially if you have someone like an AP Moira.
- [Champion's Kit](item_8682f8c7-8811-439b-8d50-fa81cd43ddce) is another option for more damage if you can afford it.
